<biogHist>
<abstract>Villa Maria Family Group Home, run by the Sisters of Charity, opened in 1964. It provided cottage accommodation to children who had been placed there by their parents or who were wards of the state. Initially the home was in New Town. It moved to Howrah in 1967. Villa Maria closed in 1982.</abstract>
<p>St Joseph's Orphanage, also known as Aikenhead House after 1958, run by the Sisters of Charity, established Villa Maria and then managed it until 1970. St Joseph's Childcare Centre, also run by the Sisters, managed the Home between 1970 and 1978.</p>
<p>In Howrah, Villa Maria was in a two storey brick house with an iron roof. It had timber floors and one internal staircase. There were six rooms on the ground floor.</p>
<p>Villa Maria had two home mothers and seven to eight children. The Sisters attempted to keep siblings together in this Home.</p>
